	<strong>Australia Adopts Updated Standard for Children's Nightwear and Limited Daywear Garments</strong>
	<p>On April 18, 2017, the new <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Details/F2017L00452" target="_blank">Consumer Goods Safety Standard 2017 related to children’s nightwear and limited day daywear</a> entered into force. The safety standard adopts updated standard AS/NZS 1249: 2014 Children's Nightwear and Limited Daywear Having Reduced Fire Hazard and will revoke previous regulations published in 2007.</p>
	<a href="/regulatory-updates/en/May-2017/#may2017-australia-standard-children-garments" class="recapViewStory" style="float:right;">View Story</a>
	<a href="javascript://" class="learnmore" style="float:left;">Read More</a>
	<div style="clear:both;"></div>
	<div class="moretext">
		<p>The standard addresses flammability and safety issues related to children's nightwear. There is a period of one year for transitioning from the 2008 regulation to the 2017 regulation. Therefore, a person may comply with either the 2003 or 2014 version of the AS/NZS 1249 standard for products until January 1, 2020.</p>
	</div><br />
